es Economics Newsletter Economics Newsletter Departmental Activities Departmental Activities Policies   Forms Policies   Forms About ECBU About ECBU Faculty Faculty Open House Presentation Senior Exit Survey Alumni  97    07 survey Donna Potter Executive Secretary P   540  464 7234 F   540  464 7005 Virginia Military Institute 345 Scott Shipp Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact ECBU Open House Presentation Open House Presentation Senior Exit Survey Senior Exit Survey Alumni  97    07 survey Alumni  97    07 survey Donna Potter Executive Secretary P   540  464 7234 F   540  464 7005 Virginia Military Institute 345 Scott Shipp Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact ECBU Donna Potter Executive Secretary P   540  464 7234 F   540  464 7005 Virginia Military Institute 345 Scott Shipp Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Donna Potter         Contact ECBU Contact ECBU Honors in Economics and Business The EC BU department offers a departmental honors program  through which cadets may receive recognition of departmental honors at graduation  Requirements are that the cadet  have a 3 2 GPA overall have a 3 2 GPA in the area of research  economics or business  have a faculty mentor to supervise their research have the endorsement of the departmental honors committee prior to the research beginning have the endorsement of the department head prior to the research beginning enroll in and successfully complete either EC 470 or BU 470   see descriptions below  present the results of their research to the departmental faculty and receive the endorsement of the majority of the faculty present for the presentation EC 470  Honors Research in Economics  0 6 3 Designed for cadets pursuing independent research under the direction of a faculty member leading to departmental honors  Prerequisite  A 3 2 GPA overall and in all economics courses  Permission of instructor  department honors committee  and the department head  BU 470  Honors Research in Business  0 6 3 Designed for cadets pursuing independent research under the direction of a faculty member leading to departmental honors  Prerequisite  A 3 2 GPA overall and in all business courses  Permission of instructor  department honors committee  and the department head  Cadets enrolled in the Institute Honors program are eligible for departmental honors if they meet the criteria listed above  in addition to meeting the requirements for institute honors  Cadets who do not meet the criteria for institute honors may receive department honors      Honors in Economics and Business The EC BU department offers a departmental honors program  through which cadets may receive recognition of departmental honors at graduation  Requirements are that the cadet  have a 3 2 GPA overall have a 3 2 GPA in the area of research  economics or business  have a faculty mentor to supervise their research have the endorsement of the departmental honors committee prior to the research beginning have the endorsement of the department head prior to the research beginning enroll in and successfully complete either EC 470 or BU 470   see descriptions below  present the results of their research to the departmental faculty and receive the endorsement of the majority of the faculty present for the presentation EC 470  Honors Research in Economics  0 6 3 Designed for cadets pursuing independent research under the direction of a faculty member leading to departmental honors  Prerequisite  A 3 2 GPA overall and in all economics courses  Permission of instructor  department honors committee  and the department head  BU 470  Honors Research in Business  0 6 3 Designed for cadets pursuing independent research under the direction of a faculty member leading to departmental honors  Prerequisite  A 3 2 GPA overall and in all business courses  Permission of instructor  department honors committee  and the department head  Cadets enrolled in the Institute Honors program are eligible for departmental honors if they meet the criteria listed above  in addition to meeting the requirements for institute honors  Cadets who do not meet the criteria for institute honors may receive department honors Honors in Economics and Business The EC BU department offers a departmental honors program  through which cadets may receive recognition of departmental honors at graduation  Requirements are that the cadet have a 3 2 GPA overall have a 3 2 GPA in the area of research  economics or business  have a faculty mentor to supervise their research have the endorsement of the departmental honors committee prior to the research beginning have the endorsement of the department head prior to the research beginning enroll in and successfully complete either EC 470 or BU 470   see descriptions below  present the results of their research to the departmental faculty and receive the endorsement of the majority of the faculty present for the presentation have a 3 2 GPA overall have a 3 2 GPA in the area of research  economics or business have a faculty mentor to supervise their research have the endorsement of the departmental honors committee prior to the research beginning have the endorsement of the department head prior to the research beginning enroll in and successfully complete either EC 470 or BU 470   see descriptions below present the results of their research to the departmental faculty and receive the endorsement of the majority of the faculty present for the presentation EC 470  Honors Research in Economics  0 6 3 EC 470  Honors Research in Economics  0 6 3 Designed for cadets pursuing independent research under the direction of a faculty member leading to departmental honors  Prerequisite  A 3 2 GPA overall and in all economics courses  Permission of instructor  department honors committee  and the department head BU 470  Honors Research in Business  0 6 3 BU 470  Honors Research in Business  0 6 3 Designed for cadets pursuing independent research under the direction of a faculty member leading to departmental honors  Prerequisite  A